==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Maranatha
<hw>Mar`a*nath"a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Aramaic
<ets>m⟦amac⟧ran ath⟦amac⟧</ets>.]</ety> <def>⟦ldquo⟧Our Lord
cometh;⟦rdquo⟧ -- an expression used by St. Paul at the conclusion of
his first Epistle to the Corinthians (xvi. 22). This word has been used
in anathematizing persons for great crimes; as much as to say,
⟦ldquo⟧May the Lord come quickly to take vengeance of thy crimes.⟦rdquo⟧
See <cref>Anathema maranatha</cref>, under <er>Anathema</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>marang tree</ent>⟦br⟧
